Original "master" repos - O
Fork a github repos     - F
clone F to make a local repo - L

edit files in L

git commit     updates L
git push       updates F
pull request to get O updated

See: https://help.github.com/articles/syncing-a-fork/

     https://help.github.com/articles/configuring-a-remote-for-a-fork/
     
in L
git remote add upstream https://github.com/url-of-O

    tags L to know that it was derived from O (it already new about F)

git remote -v    to show

To bring in changes from O to L

get fetch upstream
git checkout master   to make branch
git merge upstream/master

git push to push changes to F
